<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880914-0064 </DOCNO><HL> REVIEW andamp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides: The Grandma License </HL><SO> </SO><G> EXE CNG </G><TEXT>   Attacking the Democrats' child-care bill yesterday, Ronald Reagan asserted: &quot;If you want to leave your child with his grandmother during the day, she will have to be licensed under federal standards&quot; to get federal funds. Incredibly, a Senate staffer confirmed it: &quot;How else can you design a program that receives federal funds? You just can't give federal funds out without some assurance that they are not going to be used for child neglect and abuse.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>